    "A few concerns though have been raised for GEAs (Vardy et al. 2017; Castree et al. 2020), not least the exponentially growing body of evidence from the peer-reviewed and grey literature Communicated by Wolfgang Cramer Extended author information available on the last page of the article (Stocker and Plattner 2014; Berrang-Ford et al. 2021a; Palutikof et al. 2023).",
    "A bibliometric analysis of the Web of Science has shown that the number of unique articles on climate change has grown from almost 40,000 between 2010 and 2015 to more than 57,000 between 2016 and 2021.",
